{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_170","type":"agent_message","text":"The mailbox failure explains why the actor system now gets further before stopping: `Mailboxes` is reading the entire `pekko.actor.mailbox.requirements` map from `reference.conf` and reflectively resolving those interface names. I’m going to add the whole requirement set from that config block in one patch, because fixing only `BoundedDequeBasedMessageQueueSemantics` would just force another rebuild for the next adjacent interface."}}
